      <title>What Wisdoms Are Embedded Into Movies Part 2</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WhoIsSvenWolf/~3/hNBCNbka_q4/</link>
      <comments>http://whoissvenwolf.com/1056/what-wisdoms-are-embedded-into-movies-part-2/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 29 Feb 2012 13:23:34 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>sven@whoissvenwolf.com (Sven Wolf)</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Focus]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Inspiration]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Movie Wisdom]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Sven Wolf]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[movie wisdom]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://whoissvenwolf.com/?p=1056</guid>
      <description>Do You Believe? Let go of fear and doubt. Free your mind. That is what Morpheus tells Neo (the hero) to do before he jumps over a gap so big that it would be humanly impossible to achieve that in reality. But for you that has not seen this movie, the Matrix. They are not [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/sven-wolf-a-becoming-entrepreneur/Sven_Wolf_-_a_becoming_entrepreneur-What_Wisdoms_Are_Embedded_Into_Movies_Part_2.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center><iframe width="480" height="360" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/8nm1gbMhYDY?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></center></p>
<h1>Do You Believe?</h1>
<p>Let go of fear and doubt. Free your mind.</p>
<p>That is what Morpheus tells Neo (the hero) to do before he jumps over a gap so big that it would be humanly impossible to achieve that in reality.</p>
<p>But for you that has not seen this movie, the Matrix. They are not in a reality. They are in a artificial created computer world reality. There are rules but as in games and such. The rules can be bent.</p>
<p>The same way you mind can bend. You might not be able to jump over a gap like that but what you can do is let go of fear and doubt in the real world.</p>
<p>You have limits of physics, yes and I believe that too so big DISCLAIMER: You will not be able to leap over a big gap without killing yourself <img src='http://whoissvenwolf.com/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_wink.gif' alt=';)' class='wp-smiley' /> </p>
<p>You are able to control yourself though. You have the means to make you more than you are right now. And just by reading this post you have proven to yourself that you have some belief that you can make a change in your life and you are actively searching for information to do so.</p>
<p>Information is good but it will not do you any good if you don&#8217;t apply and implement what you learn.<br />
AND, a big and. You must practice over and ove and over again to get good at it.</p>
<p>Believe me, I have practiced these things for years and I&#8217;m still learning each every time.</p>
<p>I want you to check this short clip out before continuing to read.</p>
<p><center><iframe width="480" height="360" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ZaJPNrf1DPY?rel=0" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></center></p>
<h2>You are bending, not reality</h2>
<p>How d&#8217;you like that? Pretty cool, huh?</p>
<p>I love this movie. There are so many cool realizations the be learned from this movie.</p>
<p>When you realize that yoy are the one bending you may also realize that when change your mind about something, you will see the world with different eyes and therefore your world might have changed.</p>
<p>You see? It is you who are bending but you see it differently. Pretty cool.</p>
<p>That is why you are in more control than you may have realized before.</p>
<h3>What Movies Has Given You Lessons?</h3>
<p>I would love to hear you thoughts about this post, this movie and if you have other movies that has made a difference in your life.</p>
<p>Please comment below and share you thought.</p>
<p>And until we see each other again.</p>
<p>Take care</p>
<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoIsSvenWolf/~4/hNBCNbka_q4" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
