    <item>
      <title>What Wisdom Are Embedded Into Movies? Part 1</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/WhoIsSvenWolf/~3/BXg_L9PhvS8/</link>
      <comments>http://whoissvenwolf.com/1054/what-wisdom-are-embedded-into-movies-part-1/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Feb 2012 13:01:17 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>sven@whoissvenwolf.com (Sven Wolf)</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Focus]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Inspiration]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Movie Wisdom]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Sven Wolf]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[movie wisdom]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[movies]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://whoissvenwolf.com/?p=1054</guid>
      <description>DO or DO NOT. There is no Try! The first couple of seconds sure shows us what can happens when we don&amp;#8217;t focus and concentrate. As you surely understand. Luke loses focus sees that his ship is sinking again and he begins doubting that it is possible and he automatically fails. Well of course he [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/sven-wolf-a-becoming-entrepreneur/Sven_Wolf_-_a_becoming_entrepreneur-What_Wisdom_Are_Embedded_Into_Movies_Part_1.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center><iframe src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/7YkbgvRMpW0?rel=0" frameborder="0" width="640" height="360"></iframe></center></p>
<h1>DO or DO NOT. There is no Try!</h1>
<p>The first couple of seconds sure shows us what can happens when we don&#8217;t focus and concentrate.</p>
<p>As you surely understand. Luke loses focus sees that his ship is sinking again and he begins doubting that it is possible and he automatically fails.</p>
<p>Well of course he fails! He doesn&#8217;t believe that he can do it. He limits himself by not believing.</p>
<p>Let go of all fear that is not aiding you in your survival. Let go of all doubt that is limiting you and keeping you from succeeding.</p>
<h2>&#8220;&#8230;try not. DO! Or do not. There is no try.&#8221;</h2>
<p>So what does that mean?</p>
<p>I believe that when you say &#8220;try&#8221; you immidietaly gives yourself an escape. A get-out-of-jail-free-card.</p>
<p>It lets you get away with failing. &#8220;OH at least I tried&#8221;<br />
Well, STOP TRYING! Do or do not. If you don&#8217;t leave room for failure your chances for success is a lot greater.</p>
<p>If you still failed, at least you made an effort of not letting yourself get away with &#8220;trying&#8221;.</p>
<p>I will speak more about failure later on and why failure do not exist. Why it is impossible to really fail in anything.</p>
<h3>Control</h3>
<p>We might not be connected to and able to control the force in the same matter as the Jedi&#8217;s in Star Wars are. But we are in control of ourselves. And the one who controls himself. Controls everything.</p>
<p>&#8220;I don&#8217;t believe it. That is why you fail.&#8221;<br />
&#8220;What you mind believes, you will achieve. Always and in all ways&#8221; &#8211; John M Fogg.</p>
<p>When you believe that you can get yourself out of bed you can. But if you don&#8217;t believe you can. You won&#8217;t be able to.</p>
<p>Remember. Belief is a strong &#8220;force&#8221; and a powerful ally. But can also be our greatest enemy.</p>
<p>Catch you in another post. Take care.</p>
<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoIsSvenWolf/~4/BXg_L9PhvS8" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
