      <description>Bob Yeager is my mentor and friend and I wanted to share some of my experiences on his teaching.&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/sven-wolf-a-becoming-entrepreneur/Sven_Wolf_-_a_becoming_entrepreneur-About_Bob_Yeager.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><center><br />
<object width="425" height="344" classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="undefined" /><param name="allowFullScreen" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/3JPFAC1Qn04?hl=sv&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><param name="value" value="true" /><param name="gt" value="" /><param name="object" value="" /><embed width="425" height="344" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/3JPFAC1Qn04?hl=sv&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" value="true" gt="" object="" /></object></center></p>
<h1 style="text-align: center;">Who is Bob Yeager?</h1>
<p>Bob Yeager is a guy I met over the internet and has been my mentor and my friend for almost a year now. He has been martial arts expert, internet marketer and a entrepreneur.</p>
<p>In my opinion he is THE coach. I mean, there are a lot of internet gurus out there. Some who was actually taught by Bob Yeager. I get the feeling he is a bit uncomfortable about that because what he is teaching can be abused in the wrong hands. Let me say this. If all those gurus out there are gurus. Bob Yeager is the internet Buddha. The guru of gurus.</p>
<h2 style="text-align: center;">My Mentor Bob Yeager</h2>
<p>Bob Yeager has a to me, profound way of coaching. He really keeps me on the edge and never lets me slip. I mean, he keeps me in a place where I am forced to be accountable and paying attention to what I do and want. He does not do anything for me or spoon-feed me in any way. He just gives me some insights and then he lets me come up with the answers and solutions myself.</p>
<p>Bob Yeager is an important mentor of mine and when I &#8220;grow up&#8221; I want to do what he does. Helping and leading people to their own conclusions and watch them grow into prosperity.</p>
<h3 style="text-align: center;">Bob Yeager, My Friend</h3>
<p>He is not just a professional coach and mentor, he is also my friend. We share many interests and have a lot in common. Sometimes it&#8217;s a little creapy when I look at our backgrounds and what we have done before.<br />
He is a very homourous guy and he is goofing around a lot when he teaches so it never gets dull and boring. I&#8217;m always looking forward to our classes and our 1 on 1 coaching sessions.</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter" title="Bob Yeager" src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/twitter_production/profile_images/95752030/Picture_13.jpg" alt="Bob Yeager" width="320" height="240" /></p>
<p>I&#8217;m involved in several courses of Bob Yeager and they are kick-ass courses. There is also an upcoming course which I will share more information about when It&#8217;s getting closer to launching. So stay tuned and be sure to sign up to my <a href="http://whoissvenwolf.com/">Newsletter</a> and I will keep you posted when his big course is launching.</p>
<p>I you want to know more about <span style="text-decoration: underline;">Bob Yeager</span>, just google his name.</p>
<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/WhoIsSvenWolf/~4/ctNd1p_1IE0" height="1" width="1"/>]]></content:encoded>
