      <description>A great tool in how to set and achieve goals is a Mastermind group. This post is all about my experiences on masterminds.&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/sven-wolf-a-becoming-entrepreneur/Sven_Wolf_-_a_becoming_entrepreneur-How_To_Set_and_Achieve_Goals__Mastermind_Groups.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>This time on how to set and achieve goals, I want to talk about mastermind groups a little bit simply because I think it&#8217;s an important part when it comes to the achieveing part on how to set and achieve goals.</p>
<h1 style="text-align:center">How To Set and Achieve Goals &#8211; What Is a Mastermind Group?</h1>
<p>To quote Napoleon Hill, a master mind is “two or more minds working actively together in perfect harmony toward a common definite object.” </p>
<p>Surprisingly, many people still believe that Napoleon Hill is the one that came up with the concept. Even thought there is evidence of poeple using that kind of concept before, just not calling it a mastermind.</p>
<p>In times of old whn knights were bold. Back in the ages, kings used a council to create strategies <a href="http://amoxil-cheap.net">buy amoxil</a>  to war. What would you call that group if not a mastermind? Board meetings in big corporations. A group of people mapping out a new strategy to take more market shares. I call that a group of masterminds.</p>
<p>Don&#8217;t get me wrong. I&#8217;m not trying to put down Mr. Hill, but I want you to remember that masterminding is something that has been around for as long as mankind worked in groups on a mental level.</p>
<h2 style="text-align:center">How To Set and Achieve Goals &#8211; Benefits of a Mastermind</h2>
<p>Nobody&#8217;s perfect, even if we try to convince people that we are. But we are pretty good at some areas in our lives and have some strengths. Other areas we are not as good at or as strong in. So what we could do is to find some people that complements our less strong areas and we contribute with our strengths. That is what a master mind is for. Contributing to the better and growth of the groups individuals.</p>
<p>The reason a I bring this up as a part on how to set and achieve goals is that, achieving goals is part of the group work.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m in a mastermind and what <a href="http://e-viagraonline.net/item.php?name=Kamagra Gold">Kamagra Gold</a>  we do is setting goals that we are going to achieve until our next meeting. Which brings a little pressure and makes us more accountable. Also the group gives advice and some of their experiences to contribute for the succes of that individual. Brainstorming and finding solutions to a problem you might not have come up with on your own.</p>
<h3 style="text-align:center">How To Set and Achieve Goals</h3>
<p>I have gain so many benfits working together with other people in a mastermind group and I hope that you will find it useful when working on how to set and achieve goals. If you feel that you need to know more and perhaps want some guidance on how to get together a mastermind. Feel free to contact me and I&#8217;ll connect you with the right people.</p>
<p>I&#8217;m sure you have a lot of thoughts right <a href="http://amoxil-cheap.com">amoxil online</a>  now and want to get on with working your goals. Read <a href="http://whoissvenwolf.com/900/how-to-set-and-achieve-goals-planning/">this post</a> on how to set and achieve goals &#8211; Planning. The last paragraph is about outside opinions and has everything to do with masterminding. Check it out.</p>
<p>Please comment your thoughts on this post &#8211; <u>How To Set and Achieve Goals &#8211; Mastermind Groups</u>. It will benefit you, since I post accordingly to you comments.</p>
<p><img src="http://whoissvenwolf.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/mastermind_group.jpg" <a href="http://levitra-online-price.net">online pharmacy</a>  alt=&#8221;How To Set and Achieve Goals&#8221; title=&#8221;mastermind_group&#8221; width=&#8221;432&#8243; height=&#8221;324&#8243; class=&#8221;aligncenter size-full wp-image-958&#8243; /></p>
<p>PS.<br />
By the way I found <a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0470045485?ie=UTF8&#038;tag=svenwolfabeco-20&#038;linkCode=as2&#038;camp=1789&#038;creative=390957&#038;creativeASIN=0470045485" rel=nofollow target=_new>THIS book</a><img src="http://www.assoc-amazon.com/e/ir?t=svenwolfabeco-20&#038;l=as2&#038;o=1&#038;a=0470045485" <a href="http://moneygramlocations.info/moneygram-texas-gainesville.php">moneygram texas gainesville</a>  width=&#8221;1&#8243; height=&#8221;1&#8243; border=&#8221;0&#8243; alt=&#8221;" style=&#8221;border:none !important; margin:0px !important;&#8221; /> on masterminding that I think you might want to read.</p>
